comments: I didn't use paper but there were two components to every word, the shape and the colour. Hu was for pink and gray, she was for blue and yellow except for buvise which does not include the 'h'. Wopi was circle, buvi was the pentagonal shape, zeti was the star with many arms, and gafi was the star with a few chunky arms. The hardest bit was learning the colours - I thought there would be four colours but there were only two. This also made the teamwork difficult because one word could have two options.
